\section{Results and Discussion}

\subsection{Models Validation}

The hygrothermal model developed in EnergyPlus was validated using in-situ measurements of environmental parameters collected within the case study building, specifically \gls{temp} and \gls{rh}. A parametric analysis of the \gls{ach} was conducted to identify the simulation configuration that best matched the observed conditions, with \gls{ach} values ranging from 0.25 to 0.50 h\textsuperscript{-1}. Validation was performed by comparing simulated results with measured data in three monitored spaces (Spaces 1, 2, and 3), each equipped with four sensors. Model performance was evaluated both against individual sensor readings and against the average measured values within each space for the six years (from 2018 to 2023). The accuracy of the model in representing the building's hygrothermal behaviour was assessed using the \gls{r2}, \gls{ic}, \gls{rmse}, \gls{fi} level 1, and \gls{fi} level 2. This process confirmed that the simulation results reliably reflect the actual indoor environmental conditions, thereby reinforcing the robustness of the model and the credibility of the subsequent analyses. The results of the performance metrics are relative to the average of the three spaces, and are presented in Tab.~\ref{tab:ModelValidation}.

